# Claude Code Guidelines for ${PROJECT_NAME}

## Git Commit Rules

- Use conventional commit format (feat, fix, refactor, docs, test, chore)
- Do NOT leave marker comments in code or commits (e.g., "Phase 1", "FIX XX:", etc.)
- Keep commit messages clear and descriptive
- Ask for approval before committing — show the proposed message and wait for confirmation

